A collection of production‑ready, senior‑engineer‑grade automation tools for managing AWS infrastructure using Python and Boto3.
This repository demonstrates clean architecture, safe cloud operations, structured logging, and real‑world automation patterns used in enterprise AWS environments.

Each module is designed to be:
- Reliable — predictable behavior, clear guardrails
- Maintainable — readable code, docstrings, type hints
- Secure — IAM‑aware, credential‑safe patterns
- Extensible — modular classes ready for integration into pipelines
- Cloud‑native — built on top of AWS best practices

Included Tools
This repo currently includes two foundational AWS automation utilities, both rewritten to senior‑engineering standards.

* S3 Bucket Inventory Tool
A clean, production‑ready utility for listing all S3 buckets in an AWS account.
Capabilities
- Uses AWS’s credential chain (IAM role, env vars, AWS CLI profile)
- Retrieves bucket names and creation dates
- Structured logging for observability
- Returns structured data for automation workflows
Use Case Examples
- Inventory and governance
- Cost‑optimization workflows
- Compliance audits
- Pre‑migration assessments

* EC2 Instance Lifecycle Manager
A safe, state‑aware tool for starting and stopping EC2 instances.
Capabilities
- Retrieves current instance state before acting
- Prevents unnecessary API calls
- Supports dry‑run mode for safe previews
- Structured logging and robust exception handling
- Clean separation of concerns (state retrieval, lifecycle actions)
Use Case Examples
- Scheduled start/stop automation
- Cost‑saving workflows
- Dev/test environment orchestration
- CI/CD pipeline integration

